WEBVTT

00:01.668 --> 00:04.604
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.671 --> 00:12.412
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.479 --> 00:14.714
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.781 --> 00:16.449
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.516 --> 00:18.785
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.852 --> 00:24.457
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.524 --> 00:26.359
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.426 --> 00:30.263
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.731 --> 00:32.732
<i>- Last time on "Harvey Beaks,"</i>

00:32.799 --> 00:34.134
<i>there was a Steampunk City.</i>

00:34.200 --> 00:35.468
<i>And okay, well--</i>
<i>and then it was flying.</i>

00:35.535 --> 00:37.203
<i>And then--okay,</i>
<i>it started to fall,</i>

00:37.270 --> 00:38.738
<i>but--okay, this is going</i>
<i>a little fast then.</i>

00:38.805 --> 00:40.407
<i>And then Harvey fixed it,</i>
<i>which is all good,</i>

00:40.473 --> 00:42.142
<i>and then the crystal broke,</i>
<i>yeah, yeah.</i>

00:42.208 --> 00:43.710
<i>And then he got kicked out</i>
<i>of the city--ooh!</i>

00:43.777 --> 00:45.612
<i>And then he landed in</i>
<i>Reject Town--there I am!</i>

00:45.678 --> 00:47.080
<i>And then he promised the kids</i>
<i>he could help 'em.</i>

00:47.147 --> 00:48.348
<i>Okay, wait.</i>
<i>Okay, slow down!</i>

00:48.415 --> 00:50.650
<i>Slow down!</i>
<i>What is happening?</i>

00:50.717 --> 00:53.653
<i>[exciting music]</i>

00:53.720 --> 01:01.661
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:03.897 --> 01:10.837
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:10.904 --> 01:13.506
- I spy with my little eyes

01:13.573 --> 01:14.941
something with...

01:15.008 --> 01:16.509
{\an1}steam.

01:16.576 --> 01:18.144
- It's that thing.

01:18.211 --> 01:19.345
- You're right.

01:19.412 --> 01:20.380
- What do I win?

01:20.447 --> 01:21.381
{\an3}- Pride.

01:21.448 --> 01:23.049
- [exclaiming]

01:23.116 --> 01:24.851
- We should get
to the Power Crystal mountain

01:24.918 --> 01:26.119
any minute now.

01:26.186 --> 01:28.054
- Fee, this guy's really fun.

01:28.121 --> 01:30.223
{\an3}Look, he even fixed
my head thingy.

01:30.290 --> 01:31.891
[blades whirring]

01:31.958 --> 01:33.359
- [laughing]

01:33.426 --> 01:36.896
- He just needed a little
motor oil and vinegar.

01:36.963 --> 01:38.498
- I feel brand new.

01:38.565 --> 01:40.099
Whoo-hoo!

01:40.166 --> 01:42.602
{\an1}- Wow, I've never seen Foo
so happy.

01:42.669 --> 01:44.971
{\an3}- That's the power
of friendship.

01:45.038 --> 01:47.040
{\an3}- Are you doing
a soft-shoe dance?

01:47.106 --> 01:50.043
<i>[piano music]</i>

01:50.109 --> 01:52.011
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:52.078 --> 01:55.448
- ♪ Friends make the world
a better place ♪

01:55.515 --> 01:58.151
{\an1}♪ Always there to put a smile
on your face ♪

01:58.218 --> 01:59.619
- Hey, dude, watch it.

01:59.686 --> 02:02.222
{\an3}♪ You're invading
my personal space ♪

02:02.288 --> 02:06.392
{\an1}- ♪ I can tell we're gonna
be best friends ♪

02:06.459 --> 02:09.195
- ♪ Maybe after this
we can grab a bite ♪

02:09.262 --> 02:10.196
- Where's the wrench?

02:10.263 --> 02:11.564
- ♪ Order pay-per-view ♪

02:11.631 --> 02:14.267
♪ Watch a robot fight ♪
- This is bad.

02:14.334 --> 02:16.169
{\an1}- ♪ Now you're back
and never leaving my sight ♪

02:16.236 --> 02:17.437
- Wait, what?
- ♪ I can tell ♪

02:17.504 --> 02:19.239
{\an1}♪ We're going to be
best friends ♪

02:19.305 --> 02:21.207
'Cause you'll never abandon
me again; I'll make sure of it.

02:21.274 --> 02:23.943
- ♪ All I really need's
my brother Foo and I ♪

02:24.010 --> 02:27.981
♪ Don't need no one between me
and this open sky ♪

02:28.047 --> 02:31.751
{\an1}- ♪ Hey, I made some cookies,
want to give 'em a try? ♪

02:31.818 --> 02:35.188
{\an3}- ♪ Maybe it's not so bad
to have things like friends ♪

02:35.255 --> 02:36.689
- Cookies!
- See?

02:36.756 --> 02:38.124
Being supportive and having fun

02:38.191 --> 02:39.692
is what friendship is all about.

02:39.759 --> 02:40.727
{\an3}- Back up.

02:40.793 --> 02:41.895
So friendship isn't, like,

02:41.961 --> 02:43.162
an actual ship?

02:43.229 --> 02:46.266
{\an1}- It means I got your back,
no matter what.

02:46.332 --> 02:48.368
- No matter what, huh?

02:48.434 --> 02:50.336
- Of course.

02:50.403 --> 02:53.873
- ♪ So you'll help us
with the burning trash? ♪

02:53.940 --> 02:57.143
- ♪ Or buy us ointment
if we get a rash? ♪

02:57.210 --> 02:58.912
both: ♪ Or help us steal
the candy ♪

02:58.978 --> 03:00.880
♪ From the private stash? ♪

03:00.947 --> 03:02.715
- That's against the rules,

03:02.782 --> 03:04.551
but you get the idea.

03:04.617 --> 03:08.321
{\an3}- ♪ Now I've got a friend,
and I'm flying high ♪

03:08.388 --> 03:11.391
♪ Feeling like a steam cloud
in the sky ♪

03:11.457 --> 03:13.226
- Wait, wait, are you guys
improvising songs?

03:13.293 --> 03:14.827
Why didn't anyone tell me?

03:14.894 --> 03:19.232
- ♪ I can tell we're gonna be
best friends ♪

03:19.299 --> 03:22.368
{\an3}- ♪ We can save the city,
side by side ♪

03:22.435 --> 03:25.905
{\an1}- ♪ Nothing else will ever get
between you and I ♪

03:25.972 --> 03:29.509
- ♪ Better brace yourself,
we're in for a bumpy ride ♪

03:29.576 --> 03:33.246
both: ♪ I can tell
we're gonna be best friends ♪

03:33.313 --> 03:36.849
{\an1}- ♪ I can tell we're going to be
best friends ♪

03:36.916 --> 03:38.785
both: ♪ I can tell ♪

03:38.851 --> 03:40.219
♪ We're gonna be ♪

03:40.286 --> 03:45.058
♪ Best friends ♪

03:45.124 --> 03:47.794
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:47.860 --> 03:49.329
Yeah.

03:49.395 --> 03:51.631
- One, two, three.
♪ My name is Dade and I-- ♪

03:51.698 --> 03:53.866
- Hey, look.
We're here.

03:53.933 --> 03:56.869
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

03:56.936 --> 03:58.871
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:58.938 --> 04:00.974
- Whoa.

04:01.040 --> 04:02.575
It's beautiful.

04:02.642 --> 04:05.511
This is what I imagine
a girl's closet to look like.

04:05.578 --> 04:07.580
- So we could probably
jackhammer the entire cavern,

04:07.647 --> 04:09.148
sell everything
on the black market.

04:09.215 --> 04:10.383
I've got buyers.

04:10.450 --> 04:12.752
- Shouldn't we ask
for permission?

04:12.819 --> 04:14.387
- [imitating a motor]

04:14.454 --> 04:16.122
- Um, who would we ask?

04:16.189 --> 04:17.322
There's nobody around.

04:17.390 --> 04:18.524
<i>- Greetings.</i>

04:18.591 --> 04:19.492
{\an3}- [yells]

04:19.559 --> 04:21.594
<i>- Welcome to the Crystal Cavern</i>

04:21.661 --> 04:24.397
<i>of Power, Madness, Majesty,</i>

04:24.464 --> 04:27.367
and Chaos Supreme Mountain.

04:27.433 --> 04:31.037
I am Roberts,
Keeper of the Crystals.

04:31.104 --> 04:32.438
Namaste.

04:32.505 --> 04:35.642
And you must be
the pizza delivery people.

04:35.708 --> 04:40.580
I let your manager know
that I don't believe in tipping.

04:40.647 --> 04:43.416
- Uh, actually, we just need
a Power Crystal

04:43.483 --> 04:44.584
to save our city.

04:44.651 --> 04:46.319
Is it okay if we borrow one?

04:46.386 --> 04:47.987
- Ah, yes, that's disappointing.

04:48.054 --> 04:52.158
I'm very hungry, but please,
go ahead and take

04:52.225 --> 04:54.360
any crystal you wish.

04:54.427 --> 04:55.662
- Ah, thank you, sir.

04:55.728 --> 04:58.598
See, Fee?
You just got to ask nicely.

04:58.665 --> 04:59.699
Whoa!

04:59.766 --> 05:01.401
- [laughing]

05:01.467 --> 05:04.804
I lied because I'm evil.

05:04.871 --> 05:08.808
You have awakened
the Crystal Princess.

05:08.875 --> 05:11.244
[electricity humming]

05:11.310 --> 05:12.311
all: Whoa.

05:12.378 --> 05:13.713
- Don't look directly at it.

05:13.780 --> 05:15.748
It's horrible.

05:15.815 --> 05:17.083
[crystal clanking]

05:17.150 --> 05:19.085
- Ew, who woke me up?

05:19.152 --> 05:20.887
I was dreaming about clothes.

05:20.953 --> 05:22.755
- Hello, sweetheart.

05:22.822 --> 05:27.860
Now, only one of the crystals
here is the true Power Crystal,

05:27.927 --> 05:29.662
but you must choose wisely,

05:29.729 --> 05:33.666
because the rest
lead to your doom.

05:33.733 --> 05:37.036
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:37.103 --> 05:39.105
[cackling]

05:39.172 --> 05:40.606
- I'm gonna sit on you.

05:40.673 --> 05:43.176
- Guys, we got to find
that crystal.

05:43.242 --> 05:45.144
[all screaming]

05:45.211 --> 05:46.479
- Hey.

05:46.546 --> 05:48.147
- This one gives me a good vibe.

05:48.214 --> 05:49.148
[gasps]

05:49.215 --> 05:50.283
- Harvey, I found it.

05:50.349 --> 05:51.884
- Harvey, I actually found it,

05:51.951 --> 05:54.120
{\an1}but I'm gonna let Foo
think he's right.

05:54.187 --> 05:57.256
<i>[percussive electronic music]</i>

05:57.323 --> 05:59.459
- Fabulous.

05:59.525 --> 06:01.127
{\an3}- Every time we touch
the wrong crystal,

06:01.194 --> 06:02.328
she grows bigger.

06:02.395 --> 06:04.430
{\an3}We have to be methodical
about this.

06:04.497 --> 06:06.933
{\an1}- Got it.
Touch them all.

06:06.999 --> 06:09.368
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:09.435 --> 06:10.670
[grunting]

06:10.737 --> 06:11.838
Ay-yi-yi-yi-yi.

06:11.904 --> 06:15.875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:15.942 --> 06:17.076
Yuh-oh.

06:17.143 --> 06:18.511
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:18.578 --> 06:20.480
- Maybe I should touch
the flashy one,

06:20.546 --> 06:22.048
but it knows
that it's the flashy one,

06:22.115 --> 06:23.716
so maybe I shouldn't touch it,

06:23.783 --> 06:26.586
but maybe it knows that I know
that it's the flashy one,

06:26.652 --> 06:28.254
so maybe I should touch it.

06:28.321 --> 06:31.190
[tinkling keyboard music]

06:31.257 --> 06:32.658
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:32.725 --> 06:35.328
- [gasping]

06:35.394 --> 06:36.329
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:36.395 --> 06:39.632
[yelling]

06:39.699 --> 06:42.101
[grunting]

06:42.168 --> 06:45.571
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:45.638 --> 06:48.207
- Is this seat taken?

06:48.274 --> 06:49.609
{\an3}- [grunts]

06:49.675 --> 06:51.511
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:51.577 --> 06:53.379
{\an3}- [laughing]
That was dumb.

06:53.446 --> 06:55.114
Now it's time to sit.

06:55.181 --> 06:56.983
- I'll play some sitting music.

06:57.049 --> 06:58.918
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:58.985 --> 07:01.687
Before we get squished
by a crystal butt,

07:01.754 --> 07:03.556
I just want you guys to know

07:03.623 --> 07:05.825
I'm glad we became friends.

07:05.892 --> 07:07.160
- Huh?
Friends?

07:07.226 --> 07:08.227
What's that?

07:08.294 --> 07:09.428
- Oh, you know.

07:09.495 --> 07:11.430
Friends put a smile
on your face

07:11.497 --> 07:13.332
and make the world
a better place.

07:13.399 --> 07:15.067
- Oh, I have those.

07:15.134 --> 07:16.936
See?

07:17.003 --> 07:18.304
- No, princess.

07:18.371 --> 07:21.374
Real friends are people
who always have your back.

07:21.440 --> 07:23.442
There are all types
of friends out there.

07:23.509 --> 07:25.645
Friends that share
their motor oil,

07:25.711 --> 07:27.513
friends who look out for you,

07:27.580 --> 07:30.583
and friends who take you
on an airship that has a face.

07:30.650 --> 07:32.118
A face, you guys.

07:32.185 --> 07:34.020
A face.

07:34.086 --> 07:35.154
[bones rattling]

07:35.221 --> 07:36.322
- Hmm.

07:36.389 --> 07:37.957
- You know, if you want,

07:38.024 --> 07:39.458
you could be our friend.

07:39.525 --> 07:42.161
[all whispering]
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

07:42.228 --> 07:45.198
- Really?
You--you mean it?

07:45.264 --> 07:46.532
Oh, my cogs!

07:46.599 --> 07:49.368
- I mean, if you can handle
this much zazz,

07:49.435 --> 07:51.337
then, yeah, I guess.

07:51.404 --> 07:53.606
- "Zazz" what friends are for.

07:53.673 --> 07:56.342
Maybe you could help us
find the Power Crystal.

07:56.409 --> 07:58.344
- Oh, okay,
it's just right here.

07:58.411 --> 08:00.079
- Princess, wait.

08:00.146 --> 08:01.848
Don't show them the--

08:01.914 --> 08:05.017
oh, oh, I can't say no to you.

08:05.084 --> 08:07.520
{\an3}- There, now I'm, like,
the best friend ever.

08:07.587 --> 08:09.956
{\an1}- [gasps]
Now we can fix the city.

08:10.022 --> 08:11.490
[both cheering]

08:11.557 --> 08:12.558
- Yep, appreciate it.

08:12.625 --> 08:13.893
Whoa, look at the time.

08:13.960 --> 08:14.961
We better skedaddle.

08:15.027 --> 08:16.362
{\an3}[whispering]
Go, go, go, go, go.

08:16.429 --> 08:18.231
- Wait, no, I'm coming too.

08:18.297 --> 08:19.532
Daddy, I'm moving out.

08:19.599 --> 08:21.033
Give me credit cards.

08:21.100 --> 08:24.303
{\an3}- [crying]
My little girl is all grown up.

08:24.370 --> 08:26.072
- Um, the thing is,

08:26.138 --> 08:28.307
I don't think you're gonna fit
on my ship.

08:28.374 --> 08:30.343
- Okay, rude.

08:30.409 --> 08:32.879
[electricity humming]

08:34.679 --> 08:37.183
There are crumbs in this pocket.
They're mine now.

08:37.250 --> 08:38.484
I'm not sharing.

08:38.551 --> 08:39.485
[munching]

08:39.552 --> 08:42.355
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:42.421 --> 08:44.023
- Yeah, we got
the crystals.

08:44.090 --> 08:45.625
[all cheering]

08:45.691 --> 08:47.894
{\an3}- I was thinking we'd have
to just blow up that mountain,

08:47.960 --> 08:49.762
{\an3}but I guess
you were right, Harvey.

08:49.829 --> 08:52.431
This friendship thing really
does make some things better.

08:52.498 --> 08:54.567
{\an1}- I'm steering the ship
with my body.

08:54.634 --> 08:56.235
- Now that we have
the Power Crystal,

08:56.302 --> 09:00.573
we'll just stop and pick up
our friends in Reject Town.

09:00.640 --> 09:03.542
<i>[somber music]</i>

09:03.609 --> 09:06.612
[people screaming]

09:06.679 --> 09:10.583
- Ah-bazap, ah-bazap, ah-bazap!

09:10.650 --> 09:11.984
Flower bazap.

09:12.051 --> 09:15.254
- [crying]
Not the flowers, no.

09:15.321 --> 09:18.591
[people screaming]

09:18.658 --> 09:19.625
- What's going on?

09:19.692 --> 09:22.328
Why is everything on fire?

09:22.395 --> 09:24.430
<i>- Hello, Harvey.</i>

09:24.497 --> 09:25.865
- Mayor Moff?

09:25.932 --> 09:28.034
<i>- You like my cool</i>
<i>hologram technology?</i>

09:28.100 --> 09:30.369
<i>Well, I can afford it,</i>
<i>because I have a credit card</i>

09:30.436 --> 09:32.371
<i>with a $500 limit.</i>

09:32.438 --> 09:33.706
<i>Jealous much?</i>

09:33.773 --> 09:35.341
- My friends and I
found a Power Crystal

09:35.408 --> 09:36.742
that can save the city.

09:36.809 --> 09:38.844
<i>- You're not saving</i>
<i>doodley-squat.</i>

09:38.911 --> 09:41.213
<i>Get him, boys.</i>

09:41.280 --> 09:42.214
- What?

09:42.281 --> 09:43.215
- [laughing]

09:43.282 --> 09:45.518
Now we have the Power Crystal,

09:45.584 --> 09:48.387
{\an1}and you have
a two-day-old baguette.

09:48.454 --> 09:50.589
Joke's on you, sucker.

09:50.656 --> 09:52.358
- Wait.
Stop!

09:52.425 --> 09:56.629
<i>- Looks like your dumb little</i>
<i>plans are ruined, gear boy,</i>

09:56.696 --> 09:58.965
<i>and I'll let you in</i>
<i>on a little secret.</i>

09:59.031 --> 10:00.333
<i>It was me.</i>

10:00.399 --> 10:02.601
<i>I sabotaged the crystal</i>

10:02.668 --> 10:04.503
<i>and blamed you,</i>

10:04.570 --> 10:05.671
<i>and it worked.</i>

10:05.738 --> 10:08.240
- So it wasn't my fault?

10:08.307 --> 10:10.643
- Ooh, this is getting juicy.

10:10.710 --> 10:12.578
<i>- [cackling]</i>

10:12.645 --> 10:13.980
<i>- Oh, jeez, sorry.</i>

10:14.046 --> 10:15.448
{\an1}<i>I didn't know you were</i>
<i>in the bathroom.</i>

10:15.514 --> 10:16.849
{\an3}<i>- Get out!</i>
<i>I'm not done.</i>

10:16.916 --> 10:19.685
<i>I--I ate a lot of steam wings.</i>

10:19.752 --> 10:21.320
- You won't get away with this.

10:21.387 --> 10:23.089
We'll expose your plan.

10:23.155 --> 10:26.859
<i>- But how will you get here</i>
<i>if you don't have a ship?</i>

10:26.926 --> 10:28.828
<i>[whispering]</i>
<i>Fredd Bots, blow up the ship.</i>

10:28.894 --> 10:29.996
- What?

10:30.062 --> 10:30.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:31.063 --> 10:33.399
all: Ah-bazap!

10:33.466 --> 10:34.433
[explosion]

10:34.500 --> 10:37.136
- No!
My ship.

10:37.203 --> 10:39.772
<i>- Have fun living</i>
<i>in your dump town.</i>

10:39.839 --> 10:42.174
<i>Good-bye.</i>
<i>I hate you.</i>

10:42.241 --> 10:45.544
- [stammering]

10:45.611 --> 10:46.545
[groans]

10:46.612 --> 10:47.980
But...

10:49.415 --> 10:52.118
No!

10:52.184 --> 10:53.119
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:55.688 --> 10:56.655
<i>[somber music]</i>

10:56.722 --> 10:59.258
- Flowers, flowers, flowers.

10:59.325 --> 11:00.359
{\an1}- Aww.

11:00.426 --> 11:01.660
- I didn't think
it was possible,

11:01.727 --> 11:04.296
but Reject Town just got worse.

11:04.363 --> 11:06.098
- What are we gonna do now?

11:06.165 --> 11:07.099
- Nothing.

11:07.166 --> 11:08.167
[all gasp]

11:08.234 --> 11:09.635
- This is all my fault.

11:09.702 --> 11:11.504
I lost the Power Crystal.

11:11.570 --> 11:14.140
I lost your chance
for a better home.

11:14.206 --> 11:16.142
I even lost your current home.

11:16.208 --> 11:17.643
I lost it all.

11:17.710 --> 11:20.112
{\an3}- That's a steaming pile
of steam dookie.

11:20.179 --> 11:21.547
You think you've lost it all,

11:21.614 --> 11:25.284
{\an3}but you haven't lost
the most important thing:

11:25.351 --> 11:26.385
{\an3}us.

11:26.452 --> 11:28.354
♪ Ships come and go ♪

11:28.421 --> 11:31.257
{\an3}♪ Get zapped up
and will blow up ♪

11:31.323 --> 11:34.427
♪ Into flames sometimes ♪

11:34.493 --> 11:37.797
{\an3}♪ But you think that was
my only ship? ♪

11:37.863 --> 11:38.864
{\an3}Oh, no.

11:38.931 --> 11:40.833
♪ We still have ♪

11:40.900 --> 11:44.870
♪ The friendship kind ♪

11:44.937 --> 11:47.306
[guitar strumming]

11:47.373 --> 11:51.210
♪ It supports you
like your mother ♪

11:51.277 --> 11:56.082
♪ It makes
our poor hearts sing ♪

11:56.148 --> 12:00.286
♪ We won't give up
on each other ♪

12:00.352 --> 12:02.321
♪ 'Cause friendship ♪

12:02.388 --> 12:07.426
♪ Can do anything ♪

12:07.493 --> 12:08.828
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:08.894 --> 12:10.696
- ♪ It can lift you up ♪

12:10.763 --> 12:13.599
♪ When ya stumble ♪

12:13.666 --> 12:17.303
{\an3}- ♪ Heed the call
when you ring ♪

12:17.369 --> 12:18.971
- ♪ Feed you empanadas ♪

12:19.038 --> 12:21.941
♪ When your tummy rumbles ♪

12:22.007 --> 12:26.112
all: ♪ 'Cause friendship
can do ♪

12:26.178 --> 12:28.581
♪ Anything ♪

12:28.647 --> 12:30.649
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:30.716 --> 12:34.920
- ♪ That Moff guy's a big jerk
with power like a king ♪

12:34.987 --> 12:40.059
♪ But, Harvey, we've something
only friendship can bring ♪

12:40.126 --> 12:41.494
Do you know why?

12:41.560 --> 12:43.829
- ♪ 'Cause friendship ♪

12:43.896 --> 12:47.867
♪ Can do anything ♪

12:47.933 --> 12:50.169
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:50.236 --> 12:51.570
We're going to Steamberg,

12:51.637 --> 12:53.706
and nothing's gonna stop us.

12:53.772 --> 12:54.974
Everybody to the ship.

12:55.040 --> 12:58.277
[all cheering]

12:58.344 --> 13:00.412
- Oh, yeah.

13:00.479 --> 13:02.748
{\an1}- It's too bad we can't just
make another ship

13:02.815 --> 13:05.918
out of all this garbage.

13:05.985 --> 13:07.786
both: Or can we?

13:07.853 --> 13:09.355
- Can we?

13:09.421 --> 13:13.492
all: ♪ Desert you
it will never ♪

13:13.559 --> 13:17.596
♪ But fly us like wings ♪

13:17.663 --> 13:22.301
♪ It will carry us forever ♪

13:22.368 --> 13:24.403
♪ 'Cause friendship ♪

13:24.470 --> 13:28.974
♪ Can do anything ♪

13:29.041 --> 13:31.243
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:31.310 --> 13:33.212
♪ Friendship ♪

13:33.279 --> 13:38.484
♪ Can do anything ♪

13:38.551 --> 13:43.289
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:43.355 --> 13:45.090
<i>- [laughing]</i>
<i>Irving.</i>

13:45.157 --> 13:46.825
Can we use my new crystal?

13:46.892 --> 13:47.860
Are you ready?

13:47.927 --> 13:49.128
- Yep, all set, buddy.

13:49.195 --> 13:50.563
Toss it here.

13:50.629 --> 13:51.864
[stammering]

13:51.931 --> 13:54.400
{\an3}Ooh, man, that could've been
really bad.

13:54.466 --> 13:55.834
[crystal humming]

13:55.901 --> 13:58.837
[metal clanking]

13:58.904 --> 14:01.907
[steam hissing]

14:01.974 --> 14:03.409
- The city's floating away.

14:03.475 --> 14:04.810
We need more power.

14:04.877 --> 14:06.078
[metal squeaking]

14:06.145 --> 14:08.013
Just set her down
over there, Fee.

14:08.080 --> 14:09.715
Nice and easy.

14:09.782 --> 14:12.818
Easy, easy, easy.

14:12.885 --> 14:14.386
[crash]

14:14.453 --> 14:16.956
- Ah, this is the life.

14:17.022 --> 14:18.357
The city is running smooth,

14:18.424 --> 14:20.693
{\an1}and us buddies have
all the time in the world

14:20.759 --> 14:21.994
just to hang.

14:22.061 --> 14:23.295
- I still can't help feeling bad

14:23.362 --> 14:24.930
{\an3}about what happened
to my apprentice.

14:24.997 --> 14:26.699
I mean, I'm not really sure why,

14:26.765 --> 14:28.767
{\an3}but he kind of
felt like a son to me.

14:28.834 --> 14:31.237
{\an1}- Irving, I told you
never to mention that boy

14:31.303 --> 14:32.638
in my presence again.

14:32.705 --> 14:34.873
I mean, it's all very sad,

14:34.940 --> 14:36.375
but the boy's gone forever.

14:36.442 --> 14:38.711
<i>- Attention,</i>
<i>citizens of Steamberg.</i>

14:38.777 --> 14:39.511
{\an1}- What?

14:39.578 --> 14:41.013
- Attention, please,

14:41.080 --> 14:42.448
um, up here.

14:42.514 --> 14:44.149
{\an1}- [groans]
It's the boy.

14:44.216 --> 14:46.719
{\an1}I spotted it
with my bigoggulars.

14:46.785 --> 14:50.889
- Mayor Moff has been involved
in questionable activities.

14:50.956 --> 14:51.890
[all gasp]

14:51.957 --> 14:53.459
- Is he stealing newspapers?

14:53.525 --> 14:55.761
Because someone keeps stealing
my newspaper.

14:55.828 --> 14:57.029
- Uh, no,

14:57.096 --> 14:59.965
but he intentionally
sabotaged Steamberg

15:00.032 --> 15:01.500
and caused it to crash.

15:01.567 --> 15:03.936
Plus, he attacked all my friends
in Reject Town.

15:04.003 --> 15:06.639
- Don't worry.
Most of us survived.

15:06.705 --> 15:09.942
- I can't believe an elected
official did something corrupt.

15:10.009 --> 15:11.410
- Is everything he said true?

15:11.477 --> 15:14.446
{\an1}- So I framed a child
for a crime.

15:14.513 --> 15:16.548
{\an1}[chuckles]
We've all done it.

15:16.615 --> 15:17.850
- I can't believe it.

15:17.916 --> 15:20.919
My apprentice was innocent
this whole time.

15:20.986 --> 15:21.920
I'm sorry, Moff,

15:21.987 --> 15:23.455
but I--I can't hang out

15:23.522 --> 15:24.623
with you anymore.

15:24.690 --> 15:26.825
- [gasps]
But, no, Irving, please.

15:26.892 --> 15:28.961
Come back.
We can get through this.

15:29.028 --> 15:31.864
{\an1}- Oh, Harvey, I'm so sorry
we flung you out of the city.

15:31.930 --> 15:34.366
{\an1}I still hope you would consider
being my apprentice.

15:34.433 --> 15:35.868
- I'd love to.

15:35.934 --> 15:38.037
all: Aww.
- That's nice.

15:38.103 --> 15:40.973
- Okay, now I'm upset.

15:41.040 --> 15:43.309
Fredd Bots, assemble.

15:43.375 --> 15:45.477
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:45.544 --> 15:47.646
[panicked murmuring]

15:47.713 --> 15:50.549
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:50.616 --> 15:52.451
I want every rotten child

15:52.518 --> 15:55.421
thrown out of my city
immediately!

15:55.487 --> 15:56.488
- Fredd Bots,

15:56.555 --> 15:58.090
initiate synchronized

15:58.157 --> 16:00.025
tactical attack removal.

16:00.092 --> 16:01.226
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:01.293 --> 16:03.429
all: Bazap, bazap, bazap.

16:03.495 --> 16:05.230
[all screaming]

16:05.297 --> 16:06.231
- Come on, guys.

16:06.298 --> 16:07.232
We deserve to be here

16:07.299 --> 16:08.233
as much as anyone,

16:08.300 --> 16:09.802
and we're not leaving.

16:09.868 --> 16:12.371
[all yelling]

16:12.438 --> 16:14.907
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:14.973 --> 16:16.308
- Hiyah, hiyah, hiyah!

16:16.375 --> 16:17.710
[lasers firing]

16:17.776 --> 16:20.079
{\an1}- A'ight, tin-girl.
Let's do this.

16:20.145 --> 16:22.381
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:22.448 --> 16:24.083
- [yelling]

16:24.149 --> 16:26.819
- Yah, yah, yah!

16:26.885 --> 16:29.254
[lasers firing]

16:29.321 --> 16:31.790
That was for the flowers.

16:31.857 --> 16:32.791
- Wow.

16:32.858 --> 16:33.926
- [grunting]

16:33.992 --> 16:34.927
{\an1}Uh-oh.

16:34.993 --> 16:36.762
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:36.829 --> 16:37.796
[laser fires]

16:37.863 --> 16:39.832
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:39.898 --> 16:41.333
[crystal humming]

16:41.400 --> 16:42.735
[gears grinding]

16:42.801 --> 16:44.303
[all screaming]

16:44.370 --> 16:45.504
- Not again.

16:45.571 --> 16:46.805
[people skidding on floor]

16:46.872 --> 16:48.640
{\an1}- Harvey, we have
to do something fast.

16:48.707 --> 16:50.409
Get to the control panel.

16:50.476 --> 16:51.443
Here, take this gear.

16:51.510 --> 16:52.978
You fixed it before.

16:53.045 --> 16:54.012
- This is a washer.

16:54.079 --> 16:55.381
- There's no time!
Shut up.

16:55.447 --> 16:56.949
Go, go, go.

16:57.015 --> 16:59.418
- Oh, I don't think so.

16:59.485 --> 17:05.758
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:05.824 --> 17:06.625
Ha!

17:06.692 --> 17:08.227
Yeah, that's right.

17:08.292 --> 17:10.462
My tower expands and whatnot.

17:10.529 --> 17:12.131
Super cool, huh?

17:12.196 --> 17:13.464
- That is cool,

17:13.531 --> 17:15.867
but I'm not gonna let it
stop me.

17:15.934 --> 17:18.369
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:18.436 --> 17:20.973
- Hey, dum-dums, over here.

17:21.039 --> 17:24.242
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:24.309 --> 17:25.877
- [yells]

17:25.944 --> 17:27.746
- Oh, yeah, as if.

17:27.813 --> 17:29.515
[roars]

17:29.581 --> 17:32.184
{\an3}You guys can't even handle
my hot body.

17:32.251 --> 17:34.019
{\an3}[grunting]

17:34.086 --> 17:37.156
- Wow, now, that's something
you don't see every day.

17:37.222 --> 17:38.290
What?

17:38.357 --> 17:39.491
{\an3}- [grunts]
It won't fit.

17:39.558 --> 17:41.093
[metal clanking]

17:41.160 --> 17:43.862
- Stop right there.

17:43.929 --> 17:46.298
You're not playing hero again.

17:46.365 --> 17:47.599
{\an3}- Please.

17:47.666 --> 17:48.767
{\an3}You have to help me
fix this machine,

17:48.834 --> 17:50.669
or the whole city's doomed.

17:50.736 --> 17:52.905
- I don't give a darn
about this city.

17:52.971 --> 17:55.240
There's only one thing
I cared about,

17:55.307 --> 17:56.942
and you ruined him.

17:57.009 --> 18:02.114
Now face the wrath
of my steam sword.

18:02.181 --> 18:03.916
- What--what does the steam do?

18:03.982 --> 18:05.951
- It doesn't <i> do</i> anything.

18:06.018 --> 18:07.252
It just looks cool.

18:07.319 --> 18:10.155
That's the whole point
of steampunk.

18:10.222 --> 18:13.025
It's not practical!

18:13.091 --> 18:14.426
- [grunts]

18:14.493 --> 18:15.427
The gear.

18:15.494 --> 18:17.129
- You are super annoying.

18:17.196 --> 18:18.130
[metal clanking]

18:18.197 --> 18:20.098
Your gears are annoying.

18:20.165 --> 18:21.099
[metal clanking]

18:21.166 --> 18:22.301
And worst of all,

18:22.367 --> 18:24.803
you stole my best friend.

18:24.870 --> 18:27.973
[grunting, metal clanking]

18:28.040 --> 18:28.974
- Perfect.

18:29.041 --> 18:29.808
{\an3}Wait.

18:29.875 --> 18:31.343
Before you destroy me,

18:31.410 --> 18:33.712
I just want to say I'm sorry.

18:33.779 --> 18:35.881
I'm sorry for being
a distraction.

18:35.948 --> 18:36.882
- Distraction?

18:36.949 --> 18:38.317
What are you distracting me--

18:38.383 --> 18:39.384
ow!

18:39.451 --> 18:40.986
- Do what you got to do, dude.

18:41.053 --> 18:42.387
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:42.454 --> 18:43.889
[all screaming]

18:43.956 --> 18:46.024
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:46.091 --> 18:48.293
[metal clanking]

18:48.360 --> 18:49.294
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:49.361 --> 18:50.896
[people screaming]

18:50.963 --> 18:52.831
[grunting]

18:52.898 --> 18:55.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:55.067 --> 18:56.368
[crystal humming]

18:56.435 --> 18:58.237
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:00.138 --> 19:01.840
- [groaning]

19:05.244 --> 19:06.278
- Hey, everybody.

19:06.345 --> 19:08.280
Harvey saved the city again.

19:08.347 --> 19:11.316
[all cheering]

19:11.383 --> 19:12.317
- Whoo-hoo-hoo!

19:12.384 --> 19:14.052
That's my apprentice.

19:14.119 --> 19:16.021
- That's right,
you guys live with me now,

19:16.088 --> 19:18.490
so don't act like
you're not excited.

19:18.557 --> 19:20.626
[crowd cheering]

19:20.692 --> 19:22.194
<i>- Good job, kid.</i>

19:22.261 --> 19:25.264
<i>[somber music]</i>

19:25.330 --> 19:27.466
{\an1}- Did you come
to rub it in my face

19:27.533 --> 19:29.201
how you're better than me?

19:29.268 --> 19:30.736
Congratulations.

19:30.802 --> 19:34.006
{\an3}- I just don't understand
why you did all this.

19:34.072 --> 19:36.508
I mean, why did you act like...

19:36.575 --> 19:37.776
kind of a jerk?

19:37.843 --> 19:40.212
{\an1}- I don't expect you
to understand.

19:40.279 --> 19:41.947
It's so easy for you.

19:42.014 --> 19:44.917
You have so many friends, but...

19:44.983 --> 19:47.019
but I don't have anyone now.

19:47.085 --> 19:50.489
{\an1}Oh, maybe I'm just not meant
to have friends.

19:50.556 --> 19:53.859
Anyway, take care
of Irving for me.

19:53.926 --> 19:55.594
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:55.661 --> 19:59.398
crowd: Harvey, Harvey, Harvey,
Harvey, Harvey.

19:59.464 --> 20:01.199
- Wait, Moff, come back.

20:01.266 --> 20:05.270
crowd: Harvey, Harvey, Harvey,
Harvey, Harvey.

20:05.337 --> 20:06.838
- What?
Steam?

20:06.905 --> 20:10.409
[coughing]
<i>- Harvey, Harvey, Harvey.</i>

20:10.475 --> 20:11.677
Harvey?
- [groans]

20:11.743 --> 20:14.346
Steamberg, Dreamberg...

20:14.413 --> 20:16.248
Huh?
Where am I?

20:16.315 --> 20:18.350
- You spent the day
at Moff's, remember?

20:18.417 --> 20:22.220
- I did?

20:22.287 --> 20:23.589
Oh, yeah.

20:23.655 --> 20:26.692
I guess it was all a dream.

20:26.758 --> 20:28.827
Wait a minute.

20:28.894 --> 20:30.696
[gasps]
Hold on, Dad,

20:30.762 --> 20:33.498
I have to do something
really quick.

20:33.565 --> 20:34.933
- Irving, you're back!

20:35.000 --> 20:37.436
I saw you standing outside
and started standing

20:37.502 --> 20:38.870
by the door,
just in case you--

20:38.937 --> 20:40.539
oh, it's just you.

20:40.606 --> 20:41.607
- Hey, Moff.

20:41.673 --> 20:43.542
I know you've been feeling

20:43.609 --> 20:44.676
bummed out lately,

20:44.743 --> 20:47.279
{\an3}but I, uh--
I thought maybe

20:47.346 --> 20:48.380
this would cheer you up.

20:48.447 --> 20:50.148
It's steampunk, right?

20:50.215 --> 20:51.883
- Uh, yes,

20:51.950 --> 20:53.785
gears are very steampunk.

20:53.852 --> 20:55.621
This one--oh,
this one's kind of

20:55.687 --> 20:58.657
extra steamy-punky, actually.

20:58.724 --> 21:00.025
[chuckling]

21:00.092 --> 21:02.094
Well, thank you.

21:02.160 --> 21:03.362
- Come on, kiddo.

21:03.428 --> 21:04.696
We should probably
be getting home soon.

21:04.763 --> 21:06.098
- Actually, Dad,

21:06.164 --> 21:07.899
{\an3}why don't you stay at Moff's
for a bit?

21:07.966 --> 21:10.268
I've got a bunch of kid stuff
to do, anyway.

21:10.335 --> 21:13.005
{\an3}- Well, it looks like I can
hang out today after all.

21:13.071 --> 21:14.406
This'll be fun, huh, buddy?

21:14.473 --> 21:16.241
You and me, just like old times.

21:16.308 --> 21:20.379
{\an1}- Uh, yes, just the--
just the two of us.

21:20.445 --> 21:22.648
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:22.714 --> 21:24.182
{\an1}Hey, kid!

21:24.249 --> 21:25.183
- Huh?

21:25.250 --> 21:26.184
- Here.

21:26.251 --> 21:27.185
- What was that?

21:27.252 --> 21:28.353
[grunts]

21:28.420 --> 21:29.688
- Oh, jeez, I'm sorry.

21:29.755 --> 21:31.556
You were supposed to catch that.

21:31.623 --> 21:32.891
{\an3}- [chuckles]
It's okay.

21:32.958 --> 21:35.127
- Look, I, um--I was thinking.

21:35.193 --> 21:38.096
Why--why don't you, you know,
stay and we can all...

21:38.163 --> 21:39.031
hang out?

21:39.097 --> 21:40.265
You know, sort of together.

21:40.332 --> 21:42.634
- Really?
Can Fee and Foo come too?

21:42.701 --> 21:44.269
both: Can we?

21:44.336 --> 21:45.504
[eyeglass shatters]

21:45.570 --> 21:47.372
- Sure.

21:47.439 --> 21:50.375
[both laughing]

21:51.677 --> 21:52.744
<i>[video game beeping]</i>

21:52.811 --> 21:55.881
<i>- Hey, Irving, that's cheating!</i>

21:55.947 --> 21:59.084
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

22:02.154 --> 22:05.290
{\an8}<i>[cheerful music]</i>

22:05.357 --> 22:13.298
{\an7}<i>♪ ♪</i>
